name: alpha-amylase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Endohydrolysis of (1->4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in polysaccharides containing three or more (1->4)-alpha-linked D-glucose units
comment: Acts on starch, glycogen and related polysaccharides and oligosaccharides in a random manner; reducing groups are liberated in the alpha-configuration. The term "alpha" relates to the initial anomeric configuration of the free sugar group released and not to the configuration of the linkage hydrolysed.

references.title: alpha-Amylases.
references.journal: In: Boyer, P.D., Lardy, H. and Myrback, K. (Eds.), The Enzymes, 2nd ed., vol. 4, Academic Press, New York, 1960, p. 313-343.

references.title: Enzymic synthesis and degradation of starch and glycogen.
